[[Aotearoa]] meaning long white cloud, from ''ao'', cloud, daytime, world, ''tea'', white, and ''roa'', long, tall in [[Maori]].

Probably a reference to the appearance of mountainous land when seen on the horizon from a canoe after an ocean voyage. 

Allegedly the first English language mention was in the February 1916 New Zealand School Journal (King, 2004).